This paper is primarily focused on object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes a novel network architecture and training scheme, which involves machine learning techniques such as parameter sharing and sampling, making it relevant to subcategories such as cs.AI (artificial intelligence) and cs.LG (machine learning). Additionally, the paper discusses the computational efficiency of the proposed method, which could be relevant to subcategories such as cs.NE (neural and evolutionary computing) and cs.RO (robotics).
